The paper deals with feature selection in high-dimensional datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also discusses the use of Apache Spark, a popular big data platform, which suggests the category cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper proposes a distributed implementation of the feature selection framework, which involves parallel computing and optimization, indicating the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
